    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the island territory of Guam. For a time the term was synonymous with the indigenous Chamorro people of Guam, however, in recent decades, the term's meaning has expanded to be more ethnically ambiguous, and refers to any resident of Guam, with "Chamorro" being distinct.</Note_Text>
